title.title: 19:25 hours - Transport for London travel update

texts: Incidents at Warren St, Oval and Shepherd's Bush (Hammersmith & City) stations this afternoon have resulted in service suspension and disruption to parts of the London Underground network. These three stations remain closed.
We are working hard to restore services as quickly as possible.
Services are currently operating as follows:
District - suspended between Edgware Road and High Street Kensington (due to 7 July incidents)
Hammersmith & City - suspended (due to 7 and 21 July incidents)
Metropolitan - suspended between Moorgate to Aldgate (due to 7 July incidents)
Northern - suspended between Stockwell and Kennington (due to 21 July incidents)
Piccadilly -operating between Cockfosters and Arnos Grove only (due to 7 and 21 July incidents)
Victoria line - operating between Walthamstow to Highbury & Islington and between Victoria to Brixton (due to 21 July incidents)
